Late April, early May, Arizona deserts in Rex, five rolls of film shot, one niece absolutely adored, countless fun with friends, our second tiki event vended, and endless love for Michael✔️

In life we’ll face many moments of disbelief, despite our best efforts of anticipating, control, and planning. Some of the moments hit like a sucker punch to the gut, unpleasantly disrupting our placid expanse. And some moments appear like pure magic and perch before us like this hummingbird on a branch at sunset, begging you to remember the precious times of wonder awaiting you still.

Sometimes you’re the soft, vulnerable, vibrant flower budding in the desert and sometimes you’re a cactus covered in spines, surviving with sharp walls designed to keep you safe. You’re allowed both. But I hope your world right now is one that lets you bloom in the safe space you always deserved.

If you ask me, June 9th is one of the greatest days in history because on this day in 2016 I met Michael Gribbin; the happiest surprise that has become my best friend, husband, greatest love, and most wonderful teammate and partner I could have EVER found. Navigating life and growing together is FUN and an honor, and caring for you is such a privilege. Grateful is an understatement. Frick, I love you🤍

You don’t have to try to summarize or make sense of the year you just lived if that doesn’t feel right for you. The end of a year doesn’t require a condensed definition, and I promise nobody magically feels brand new on January 1st. But I hope you feel hopeful and encouraged and peaceful right now and in many of 2024’s 366 days🤍
